    "---\n",
    "## 12. Summary & Next Steps\n",
    "\n",
    "### What This Notebook Achieved\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Data Pipeline**: Downloaded (or generated) options chain data with bid/ask, Greeks, and IV\n",
    "2. **Surface Construction**: Built a clean OTM IV surface across multiple expiries\n",
    "3. **Heston Calibration**: Applied differential evolution + local refinement to fit Heston parameters to the surface\n",
    "4. **Mispricing Detection**: Identified strikes where market IV deviates from Heston fair value\n",
    "5. **Strategy Generation**: Built delta-hedged straddle positions on mispriced options\n",
    "6. **Backtest & P&L Attribution**: Simulated daily delta-hedging with P&L decomposition\n",
    "\n",
    "### Limitations & Improvements\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Transaction costs** are not included — bid-ask spreads will reduce P&L significantly\n",
    "- **Greeks are BS-based approximations** — full Heston Greeks require bumping the pricing function\n",
    "- **Single calibration per session** — in production, calibrate daily on a rolling window\n",
    "- **Synthetic data is noise-free** — real data will have more noise and require more robust filtering\n",
    "- **No position sizing** — allocating according to Kelly criterion or volatility targeting would improve risk-adjusted returns\n",
    "\n",
    "### Production Deployment Checklist\n",
